For this homework, we will be using the msleep dataset from the ggplot2 package. This dataset contains information about the sleep habits of various mammals. Reference: V. M. Savage and G. B. West. A quantitative, theoretical framework for understanding mammalian sleep. Proceedings of the National Academy of Sciences, 104 (3):1051-1056, 2007.

3. Make a plot that shows the number of mammals in each vore type. Which vore type is most represented in the data? The most represented vore type are herbivores

ggplot(data=msleep,
       mapping=aes(x=vore))+
  geom_bar(mapping = aes(fill = vore))+
  labs(title = "Number of Mammals in Each Vore")

6. Build a plot that shows the range of bodywt. by vore type. Because the range of bodywt is so variable, you will need to scale the y-axis. You do this by adding scale_y_log10() as another layer.

ggplot(data=msleep,
       mapping=aes(x=vore, y=bodywt))+
  scale_y_log10()+
  geom_boxplot()+
  labs(title = "Rage of Bodyweight by Vore Type")

7. Is there a relationship between body weight and total sleep time? Add appropriate labels and a title to your plot. Yes there is a relationship between body weight and total sleep time - as body weight increases, sleep time decreases.

names(msleep)
##  [1] "name"         "genus"        "vore"         "order"        "conservation"
##  [6] "sleep_total"  "sleep_rem"    "sleep_cycle"  "awake"        "brainwt"     
## [11] "bodywt"
ggplot(data=msleep,
       mapping=aes(x=bodywt,y=sleep_total))+
    scale_x_log10()+
  geom_point(mapping=aes(color=vore))+
  geom_smooth(method=lm,se=T)+
  labs(title="Body Weight vs. Total Sleep Time")
## `geom_smooth()` using formula = 'y ~ x'

8. Which vore type tends to sleep the most? Build a plot to support your answer. Insects tend to sleep the most.

ggplot(data=msleep,
